{
  "texts": [
    "The node embeddings were further processed by two-layer directed graph convolutional networks (with a hidden unit size of 128).",
    "Two-layer fully connected neural networks (where the hidden unit size was half of the input dimension size) were also included for node and pathway classification tasks to implement the pathway-guided regularization term.",
    "The GNN framework included 119,334 trainable parameters in total.",
    "The number of training epochs T was 100.",
    "The Adam optimizer was used to learn the model parameters, with a learning rate of 0.01."
  ]
}